Building the DataSet

First, visualize the current dataset:

load("Boston2015.RData")

Using dplyr for some data transformation:

library(dplyr)
library(lubridate)
library(stringr)
library("FactoMineR", lib.loc="/Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/3.5/Resources/library")
library("RcmdrPlugin.FactoMineR", lib.loc="/Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/3.5/Resources/library")
library("Rcmdr", lib.loc="/Library/Frameworks/R.framework/Versions/3.5/Resources/library")

I am going to build the dataset using the imported dataset marathon_results_2015

Boston2015SubSet <- marathon_results_2015 %>%
  filter(Age >= 20, Age <= 50, M.F == "F")

Now, I am going to transform some fields so I can use them in the PCA.

Boston2015SubSet <- Boston2015SubSet %>%
  mutate(X10ktotal = as.numeric(X10K), PaceTotal = as.numeric(Pace), 
         X5kseconds = as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(X5K, format = '%H:%M:%S'), as.POSIXct('00:00:00', format = '%H:%M:%S'), units = 'secs')),
         X10kseconds = as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(X10K, format = '%H:%M:%S'), as.POSIXct('00:00:00', format = '%H:%M:%S'), units = 'secs')),
         PaceSeconds = as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(Pace, format = '%H:%M:%S'), as.POSIXct('00:00:00', format = '%H:%M:%S'), units = 'secs')),
         OfficialTimeSeconds = as.numeric(difftime(as.POSIXct(Official.Time, format = '%H:%M:%S'), as.POSIXct('00:00:00', format = '%H:%M:%S'), units = 'secs')),
         BibNumber = str_extract(Bib, "[F]"))

So, perhaps it is not good to include all those professionals into the model since they are expected to have results that are about 3 standard deviations of the median.

Boston2015FemaleNoPro <- Boston2015SubSet %>%
  filter(is.na(BibNumber) == TRUE)

A final transformation:

Boston2015FemaleNoPro <- Boston2015FemaleNoPro %>%
  mutate(BibN = as.numeric(as.character(Bib)))
